{
  "stem": "1479.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You could see what was going on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But the most important thing-- there were survivors, people who witnessed, who were there, who could attest what we saw, what the Nazis did to our people.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For instance, you know, do you think they could-- the barracks, there were everywhere people buried.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there were signs, you know, what was going on over there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They tried to erase some barracks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They tried to erase the place where there were the hangings done.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There were many things.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were-- there was 24 hours a day going on all kind of murdering in all kind of shapes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And number one-- I-- if you do not realize-- Plaszow was not somewheres in a desert.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were in the middle of civilization where people lived all around.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They heard our cries.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They saw the smoke.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they saw everything what was going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only complaint the Polish people had-- that the stench from the burning flesh or they did not like, for instance, you know, like sometimes the trains, where they were planning to go on vacation yet the railroad tracks were busy with the cattle cars going and coming, because they was from Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Constantly, people were sended-- sended to some other death camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And people were brought from different places to Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So there was like a death factory going back and forth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So some Polish people had complaints that we were disturbing their peace and comfort.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And finally, after being a few weeks in Plaszow-- as you know when you heard about Schindler's list-- I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It is only a miracle how they did not remove the names from this list of my sister and my name, because we were right away on the Schindler's list.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
